import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['count'], data['rate'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Count')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between count and rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data = data.groupby('month')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['month'], data['count'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.axhline(data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count by month?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
